This paper involves the application of deep neural networks for audio-visual automatic speech recognition, which falls under the intersection of several computer science sub-fields. Based on the content of the abstract, the most likely sub-category is cs.SD (Sound), followed by cs.CL (Computation and Language), cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.CV (Computer Vision), and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
